WEBVTT

00:00.720 --> 00:02.950
- MY ART CLASS IS GOING
TO ITALY FOR A MONTH.

00:03.070 --> 00:04.298
I'VE DECIDED
THAT I WANT TO GO...

00:04.410 --> 00:05.377
BY MYSELF.

00:07.520 --> 00:08.896
- I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD GET MARRIED,

00:09.000 --> 00:10.513
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT I'M NOT GOING

00:10.630 --> 00:11.380
TO SUPPORT YOU IN THIS.

00:11.490 --> 00:12.388
- THAT REALLY HURT
MY FEELINGS...

00:12.490 --> 00:13.934
- I TRUST YOU,
AND I BELIEVE IN YOU.

00:14.040 --> 00:16.975
CAN WE PLEASE DO
THIS TOGETHER?

00:17.080 --> 00:19.969
- I KNOW I WAS
A REALLY GOOD SALESMAN.

00:20.080 --> 00:22.878
I'M JUST NOT SO SURE
I'M A GOOD FATHER.

00:22.980 --> 00:24.322
- YEAH.

00:24.430 --> 00:26.318
- YOU'VE BEEN DOING SUCH
A GOOD JOB WITH THESE TWO,

00:26.440 --> 00:29.364
AND I COULDN'T BE ABLE TO DO
WHAT I'M DOING WITHOUT YOU.

00:29.470 --> 00:31.882
THANK YOU.

00:31.990 --> 00:33.127
- I LIKE YOU.

00:33.240 --> 00:35.026
LIKE, MORE THAN JUST FRIENDS.

00:35.130 --> 00:36.233
- OH.

00:40.660 --> 00:43.584
[knocking]

00:47.010 --> 00:49.899
- HEY.

00:50.010 --> 00:51.113
- HEY, YOU.

00:51.220 --> 00:53.313
- WHAT'S UP?

00:53.430 --> 00:55.591
YOU NEED MY ASTRONOMY NOTES
OR SOMETHING?

00:55.710 --> 00:57.428
- NO.

00:57.540 --> 00:58.325
UM...

00:58.430 --> 01:00.182
I MIGHT BE A LITTLE DRUNK.

01:00.300 --> 01:01.870
- YEAH?
- LIKE A LITTLE.

01:01.990 --> 01:03.014
- I'M GETTING THAT, ACTUALLY.

01:03.130 --> 01:04.882
YEAH, THAT MAKES SENSE.

01:04.990 --> 01:08.289
DO YOU NEED SOMEWHERE
TO CRASH?

01:08.410 --> 01:08.922
- IS YOUR ROOMMATE HERE?

01:09.030 --> 01:12.921
- NO, HE IS NOT.

01:13.030 --> 01:15.169
- YOUR HAIR IS ALL MESSED UP.

01:15.280 --> 01:17.100
- YEAH, I WASN'T
EXPECTING YOU TO...

01:22.700 --> 01:24.930
ACTUALLY...

01:25.050 --> 01:27.359
YOU'VE BEEN DRINKING, YOU KNOW.

01:27.460 --> 01:29.803
YOU MIGHT NOT KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

01:29.910 --> 01:31.081
I DON'T WANT--

01:44.510 --> 01:45.545
- HEY, HEY.

01:45.650 --> 01:47.686
TURN MY VOCAL UP.

01:47.790 --> 01:52.409
- OH, BOY.

01:52.520 --> 01:53.316
- FORGET IT.

01:53.420 --> 01:54.819
JUST PUT IT BACK
WHERE IT WAS.

01:54.940 --> 02:00.242
- OH, BOY.

02:00.360 --> 02:01.554
- STOP.
STOP.

02:01.670 --> 02:04.184
STOP.
STOP.

02:04.290 --> 02:05.188
NOT FEELING IT.

02:05.290 --> 02:07.326
NOT FEELING IT.

02:07.430 --> 02:09.364
- WHAT EXACTLY
AREN'T YOU FEELING?

02:09.470 --> 02:10.562
- WELL, IF I KNEW THAT,

02:10.680 --> 02:13.126
THEN I'D BE FEELING IT,
WOULDN'T I?

02:13.230 --> 02:14.504
- I CANNOT ARGUE THAT POINT.

02:14.610 --> 02:15.986
DO YOU WANT TO,
MAYBE, TAKE TEN,

02:16.100 --> 02:17.055
AND RECHARGE YOUR BATTERIES,

02:17.170 --> 02:19.309
AND WE'LL COME AND TRY IT AGAIN?

02:19.410 --> 02:21.162
- NO, I DON'T NEED
TO RECHARGE MY BATTERIES, BRO.

02:21.270 --> 02:23.204
THIS IS NOT OLIVER ROME'S FAULT
RIGHT NOW.

02:23.310 --> 02:25.653
IT SOUNDS DIFFERENT
THAN WHEN WE LEFI' IT LAST NIGHT.

02:25.760 --> 02:26.829
IT SOUNDS WAY DIFFERENT.

02:26.930 --> 02:28.318
- DO YOU WANT TO COME IN,
AND HEAR THE PLAYBACK?

02:28.420 --> 02:29.512
BECAUSE I BET YOU'LL
CHANGE YOUR TUNE.

02:29.630 --> 02:30.938
- IT'S NOT GOING
TO SOUND ANY DIFFERENT

02:31.040 --> 02:33.622
BECAUSE THIS SOUNDS LIKE YOU
SLEPT ON THE BOARD LAST NIGHT,

02:33.730 --> 02:35.004
AND EVERYTHING
SOUNDS DIFFERENT.

02:35.120 --> 02:36.382
- OH, I'M THE ONE
THAT'S HALF ASLEEP.

02:36.500 --> 02:37.694
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

02:37.810 --> 02:39.459
YOU THINK JUST
'CAUSE YOU'RE PUSHING BUTTONS--

02:39.570 --> 02:40.639
- I THINK ALL THE TONES
SOUNDS LIKE CRAP.

02:40.740 --> 02:41.081
- WHOSE FAULT COULD THIS BE,
OTHER THAN YOURS?

02:41.190 --> 02:43.294
- FUN, RIGHT?

02:43.400 --> 02:46.119
- I HOPE YOU WEREN'T PLANNING
ON SLEEP TONIGHT.

02:46.230 --> 02:47.458
- ARE YOU FREAKING SERIOUS
RIGHT NOW?

02:47.580 --> 02:50.469
- OH, ROME LOST THE PORKPIE.
THAT'S NOT A GOOD SIGN.

02:50.580 --> 02:51.956
- YOU KNOW THIS? YOU SEE THIS?
THIS IS HAPPENING RIGHT NOW.

02:52.060 --> 02:53.300
- YOU KNOW I'M HAVING
A HARD TIME.

02:53.410 --> 02:55.549
- "CROSBY, I'M AFRAID
MY SONGS SUCK.

02:55.650 --> 02:57.470
AND MY FRAGILE EGO,
IT CAN'T HANDLE THAT."

02:57.590 --> 02:58.989
- "AND I'M UPSET BECAUSE I HAVE
A DEMONIC BABY AT HOME,

02:59.100 --> 03:00.920
AND I HAVEN'T SLEPT
FOR SEVEN DAYS."

03:01.040 --> 03:04.077
- "I NEED TO GET LAID, MAN.
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH MY LIFE?"

03:04.180 --> 03:05.966
- OH, MY GOD.
IT'S GETTING SERIOUS.

03:06.080 --> 03:07.240
I SHOULD GET IN THERE.

03:07.350 --> 03:08.829
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

03:08.940 --> 03:10.555
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

03:10.670 --> 03:13.355
- WHATEVER, THIS IS MY STUDIO
RIGHT NOW!

03:19.160 --> 03:20.252
- AH.

03:26.620 --> 03:28.713
[sighs]

03:40.110 --> 03:43.591
- HEY, IT'S YOUR PARTNER
IN CRIME.

03:43.700 --> 03:45.497
SO GUESS WHO JUST BESTED YOU

03:45.600 --> 03:47.215
FOR THE SHORTEST
REJECT ION EMAIL YET?

03:47.330 --> 03:51.289
"PER YOUR INQUIRY,
THE POSITION HAS BEEN FILLED."

03:51.400 --> 03:53.049
YEAH, YOU CAN FEEL
THE LOVE THERE, CAN'T YOU?

03:53.160 --> 03:56.459
ANYWAY, IT MADE ME THINK
OF YOU

03:56.580 --> 03:59.743
SO JUST THOUGHT I'D CALL.

03:59.860 --> 04:00.986
OKAY?

04:01.100 --> 04:02.408
OKAY.

04:02.510 --> 04:03.442
BYE.

04:11.490 --> 04:14.175
HEY, IT'S YOUR PARTNER
IN CRIME.

04:14.280 --> 04:16.077
SO GUESS WHO
JUST BESTED YOU

04:16.180 --> 04:18.660
FOR THE SHORTEST
REJECT ION EMAIL YET?

04:27.850 --> 04:28.771
- HEY.

04:28.880 --> 04:29.778
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

04:29.890 --> 04:31.152
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

04:31.270 --> 04:33.602
- YEAH, YEAH.
NO, EVERYTHING'S FINE.

04:33.720 --> 04:35.927
I JUST, I DON'T KNOW, I WAS
AT HOME, AND YOU WERE HERE,

04:36.030 --> 04:40.308
AND I WAS FEELING LIKE
WE WEREN'T CONNECTING.

04:40.410 --> 04:41.274
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

04:41.380 --> 04:43.029
- YEAH.

04:43.140 --> 04:46.268
I KNOW WORKING LATE IS
NOT IDEAL, BUT, YOU KNOW,

04:46.380 --> 04:50.248
UNTIL I GET OUT
FROM UNDER THIS PILE,

04:50.350 --> 04:52.762
I GOT TO KEEP UP WITH IT,
SO--

04:52.870 --> 04:54.076
IT'S SOMETHING
WE CAN TALK ABOUT,

04:54.190 --> 04:55.316
BUT THERE'S NO
OTHER WAY FOR ME

04:55.430 --> 04:58.217
TO GET OUT FROM
UNDER ALL OF THIS MESS.

04:58.330 --> 05:02.983
- I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO TALK.

05:06.300 --> 05:09.098
- NO, YOU DIDN'T.

05:09.200 --> 05:12.192
UH, WOW.
THIS IS A FIRST.

05:12.310 --> 05:13.823
- I MEAN, IF YOU
DON'T HAVE TIME...

05:13.930 --> 05:15.852
- NO, NO, I HAVE THE TIME.
- OKAY.

05:15.970 --> 05:19.098
- OKAY, LET ME JUST
BE SURE THAT'S--

05:31.150 --> 05:32.117
- OOH, OW.

05:32.220 --> 05:33.630
- I'M SORRY, I JUST--

05:33.740 --> 05:35.116
- NO, NO, IT'S FINE,
IT'S FINE, IT'S FINE.

05:35.230 --> 05:37.118
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.480
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:54.590 --> 05:57.138
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:57.250 --> 05:59.457
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

05:59.560 --> 06:01.004
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:01.110 --> 06:04.568
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:04.670 --> 06:06.900
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:07.020 --> 06:08.214
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:08.330 --> 06:11.606
FOREVER YOUNG

06:11.710 --> 06:14.224
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:14.330 --> 06:16.503
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:16.610 --> 06:18.225
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

06:18.340 --> 06:21.229
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

06:21.340 --> 06:23.228
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

06:23.340 --> 06:26.161
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:26.280 --> 06:28.100
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:28.210 --> 06:31.008
FOREVER YOUNG

06:31.110 --> 06:32.270
MAY YOU STAY

06:32.390 --> 06:34.449
FOREVER YOUNG

06:48.990 --> 06:49.888
- GOOD MORNING.

06:49.990 --> 06:52.367
- MM.

06:52.480 --> 06:56.064
- SO, UM,
THAT WAS FUN LAST NIGHT.

06:56.170 --> 06:58.024
- GOD, I'M SO HUNG OVER.

06:58.140 --> 06:59.209
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

06:59.310 --> 07:00.095
- ARE YOU WAITING
FOR ONE OF THESE?

07:00.210 --> 07:02.178
- NO, YOU CAN GO AHEAD.
- GREAT, THANK YOU.

07:07.280 --> 07:09.384
- [sighs]

07:09.490 --> 07:12.209
OKAY, WELL,
HAVE A GOOD DAY, I GUESS.

07:12.320 --> 07:16.529
- MM.

07:16.640 --> 07:19.154
- AND I PICKED UP
YOUR PRESCRIPTIONS, SO...

07:19.260 --> 07:20.249
- WELL, HOW COME
I NEED TWO BOXES?

07:20.370 --> 07:21.530
WHAT, AM I GETTING WORSE?

07:21.640 --> 07:23.016
- NO, I JUST PICKED UP
ANOTHER ONE

07:23.130 --> 07:24.574
SO YOU WOULDN'T HAVE
TO THINK ABOUT REFILLING THEM.

07:24.680 --> 07:25.817
- OH.
THANKS.

07:25.920 --> 07:26.227
- HERE, SIT DOWN FOR A MINUTE.

07:26.340 --> 07:29.309
- OKAY.

07:29.410 --> 07:31.640
- THIS IS AMEX.
- YEAH.

07:31.760 --> 07:32.715
- MORTGAGE.
- OKAY.

07:32.830 --> 07:34.400
- AND I MADE A CHEAT SHEET
FOR YOU.

07:34.520 --> 07:36.101
ALL THE NUMBERS
YOU COULD POSSIBLY NEED.

07:36.210 --> 07:39.486
THE HOTEL, OF COURSE,
WHERE I'LL BE STAYING.

07:39.590 --> 07:41.558
THE ART SCHOOL.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.104
THE BRUNSKY'S.
- WHO?

07:43.220 --> 07:44.312
- THE BRUNSKY'S.

07:44.420 --> 07:46.069
- BRUNSKY'S?
- OUR NEIGHBORS.

07:46.180 --> 07:47.078
NEXT DOOR.

07:47.190 --> 07:49.909
- OH, HUH.

07:50.020 --> 07:50.839
THIS IS VERY NICE.

07:50.950 --> 07:51.848
- ALL THE NUMBERS ARE HERE.

07:51.950 --> 07:53.497
EVERYTHING YOU COULD
POSSIBLY NEED,

07:53.610 --> 07:54.565
EXCEPT FOR THE ALARM CODE,

07:54.680 --> 07:56.329
WHICH YOU HAVE IN YOUR HEAD,
RIGHT?

07:56.440 --> 07:57.464
- GIVE ME A HINT.

07:57.580 --> 08:01.050
- OUR ANNIVERSARY.

08:01.170 --> 08:03.855
- OH.

08:03.960 --> 08:07.236
- SO, YOU'RE ALL SET,
YOU KNOW.

08:07.340 --> 08:08.546
- THANKS, HONEY.

08:08.660 --> 08:10.969
I'M ALL SET.

08:11.070 --> 08:13.413
- 'CAUSE YOU'RE GONNA BE HERE
ALL BY YOURSELF.

08:13.520 --> 08:14.179
- YEAH, I'LL BE FINE.

08:14.280 --> 08:15.201
OKAY?

08:20.560 --> 08:22.835
- ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, "MAD MAX."

08:22.950 --> 08:23.700
THIS IS GOOD.

08:23.810 --> 08:24.731
LET'S TRY THE 100 MACRO

08:24.840 --> 08:26.080
WITH THE LENS HOOD NOW.

08:26.190 --> 08:27.225
- 100 MACRO WITH LENS HOOD.

08:42.720 --> 08:47.168
WHY IS THERE A PICTURE
OF AUNT SARAH IN HERE?

08:47.280 --> 08:49.555
- WHY ARE YOU IN THERE, MAX?

08:49.660 --> 08:51.412
COME ON, HUH.
YOU GOTTA STAY OUT OF MY STUFF.

08:51.530 --> 08:52.974
- YOU TOLD ME
TO GET A LENS HOOD.

08:53.080 --> 08:54.832
- YEAH, I DID.

08:54.940 --> 08:56.043
LENS HOOD.

08:56.150 --> 08:58.357
COME ON, LET'S GO.
WE'RE ALMOST DONE.

08:58.460 --> 08:59.427
- I SAW A MOVIE
ABOUT A SERIAL KILLER.

08:59.530 --> 09:01.327
HE KEPT HIDDEN PICTURES TOO.

09:01.430 --> 09:02.351
- THEY'RE NOT HIDDEN.

09:02.470 --> 09:04.017
- ONLY HE HID THEM
UNDER HIS BED.

09:04.120 --> 09:05.052
- OKAY, THEY WEREN'T HIDDEN,
MAX. THEY'RE IN A DRAWER.

09:05.160 --> 09:08.607
- SERIAL KILLERS
ARE 91% MALE, 54 WHITE.

09:08.720 --> 09:10.540
THEIR AVERAGE I.Q. IS 113,

09:10.650 --> 09:13.471
WHICH IS CONSIDERED
ABOVE AVERAGE INTELLIGENCE.

09:13.580 --> 09:15.400
YOU'RE WHITE
AND MALE AND SMART,

09:15.520 --> 09:16.646
SO YOU COULD BE
A SERIAL KILLER.

09:16.760 --> 09:18.580
- I'M NOT
A SERIAL KILLER, MAX.

09:18.690 --> 09:20.237
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

09:20.350 --> 09:22.375
YOU GOTTA STOP WITH
ALL THE STATS AND EVERYTHING.

09:22.490 --> 09:24.378
THAT'S FROM THE INTERNET.

09:24.490 --> 09:25.866
YOU'RE ON THE INTERNET
WAY TOO MUCH.

09:25.970 --> 09:28.552
THAT WIKIPEDIA, IT'S--
UNPLUG ONCE IN A WHILE.

09:28.670 --> 09:31.696
YOU SHOULD GO OUTSIDE.
YOU'RE PALE, TOO.

09:31.810 --> 09:33.493
GET SOME SUN.

09:33.600 --> 09:34.419
- DO YOU STILL LIKE HER?

09:34.530 --> 09:35.849
- NO.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.633
NO, I LIKE HER AS A FRIEND.

09:37.740 --> 09:38.911
- IF YOU DON'T LIKE HER,

09:39.020 --> 09:40.499
THEN WHY DON'T YOU
TH ROW THE PICTURE AWAY?

09:40.610 --> 09:41.463
- BECAUSE IT'S A GOOD PICTURE

09:41.580 --> 09:43.536
AND MAYBE I JUST WANT
TO KEEP IT.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.538
- BECAUSE YOU LIKE HER.
- NO, MAX!

09:45.650 --> 09:47.811
- WELL, NOW YOU'RE
RAISING YOUR VOICE

09:47.930 --> 09:49.477
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE ANGRY
OR FRUSTRATED.

09:49.580 --> 09:53.994
- I'M NOT ANGRY.
I'M FRUSTRATED, MAYBE, YEAH.

09:54.110 --> 09:57.489
LOOK, MAX,
YOUR AUNT SARAH AND I,

09:57.590 --> 09:59.478
YEAH,
WE DID LIKE EACH OTHER ONCE,

09:59.590 --> 10:02.900
AND THEN WE STOPPED,
AND THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS.

10:03.010 --> 10:05.387
IT'S ADULT STUFF,
AND IT'S MESSY, AND IT'S WEIRD.

10:05.500 --> 10:07.832
WE WERE DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

10:07.950 --> 10:10.089
I'M CRANKY.
SHE'S FLAKY.

10:10.190 --> 10:11.418
WE BOTH HAD BAGGAGE.

10:11.540 --> 10:13.292
IT DIDN'T WORK OUT,
THAT'S THE POINT.

10:13.400 --> 10:15.960
- BAGGAGE?
- YEAH, BAGGAGE.

10:16.060 --> 10:17.152
BAGGAGE.

10:17.270 --> 10:18.362
THAT'S THE STUFF YOU BRING
INTO A RELATIONSHIP,

10:18.470 --> 10:21.121
IF YOU WANT TO RUIN IT.

10:21.240 --> 10:23.231
- THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.
SUITCASES ARE FOR TRIPS.

10:23.340 --> 10:24.989
- THAT'S RIGHT, EXACTLY RIGHT.
IT'S A TRIP.

10:25.100 --> 10:29.059
IT'S A LONG TRIP
WITH A BIG SUITCASE

10:29.180 --> 10:30.488
FILLED WITH PAIN.

10:30.590 --> 10:31.864
- THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A METAPHOR.

10:31.970 --> 10:33.244
I DON'T LIKE METAPHORS.

10:33.350 --> 10:36.035
- ALL RIGHT, WELL, THEN STAY OUT
OF MY DRAWERS.

10:41.290 --> 10:42.632
- DOES AUNT SARAH
HAVE PICTURES OF YOU?

10:42.740 --> 10:45.664
- [groans]
YOU'RE KILLING ME.

10:45.780 --> 10:46.769
- ALL RIGHT, GUYS, EAT UP.
COME GET YOUR TREAT.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.393
- MAN, YOU'RE GOOD.
THANKS.

10:48.500 --> 10:50.502
- WE JUST THINK ABOUT LUNCH
AND, BOOM, IT APPEARS.

10:50.610 --> 10:52.601
- THAT'S RIGHT,
I'M A MAGICIAN OF FOOD.

10:52.720 --> 10:53.789
- NO PINE NUTS IN THIS?

10:53.890 --> 10:54.572
- I WOULD RATHER DIE
THAN LET THERE BE

10:54.680 --> 10:56.682
A PINE NUT IN YOUR SALAD.

10:56.790 --> 10:57.927
- I WOULD KILL YOU.

10:58.030 --> 10:58.576
- YOU KNOW, I ALSO HAND PICKED
THE STRAWBERRIES

10:58.690 --> 11:00.442
IN HUMBOLDT THIS MORNING.

11:00.550 --> 11:02.165
- YOU LIVE FOR THIS, DON'T YOU?

11:02.280 --> 11:04.999
- YES, YOUR DIGESTIVE HABITS
ARE MY LIFE.

11:05.110 --> 11:06.134
- RIGHT?

11:06.250 --> 11:07.797
- THINK ABOUT IT
WHEN I GO TO SLEEP AT NIGHT.

11:07.900 --> 11:09.344
- YOU KNOW,
EVERY BAND NEEDS AN AMBER,

11:09.460 --> 11:10.529
THAT'S WHAT I THINK.

11:10.630 --> 11:12.769
- YEAH, SIGN ME UP FULL TIME.
FULL TIME.

11:12.870 --> 11:13.939
- TWO OF 'EM.
- YEAH. ALL THE TIME.

11:14.050 --> 11:14.869
- YEAH.

11:14.980 --> 11:16.379
YEAH.
- LOOK AT THIS GUY.

11:16.500 --> 11:18.559
- YEAH, YOU NEED TO, OBVIOUSLY.
- YOU HAVE A FUNNY MACHINE?

11:18.670 --> 11:20.149
WE COULD USE A FUNNY MACHINE,
ACTUALLY.

11:20.260 --> 11:21.704
- THAT WOULD BE NICE.
- THAT'D BE REAL NICE.

11:21.810 --> 11:23.391
- HI, HONEY.

11:23.510 --> 11:24.602
- HEY, RAMBO.

11:24.710 --> 11:25.642
- OLIVER...
- COME IN PEACE.

11:25.750 --> 11:26.648
- YOU GOT A SECOND?
- FREEDOM.

11:26.750 --> 11:28.479
- YOU GUYS, CAN WE TALK?
- YEAH.

11:28.580 --> 11:29.672
- GIVE IT A BREAK.

11:29.790 --> 11:30.688
HI, SORRY.

11:30.790 --> 11:31.757
HE'S THE WORST.

11:31.860 --> 11:34.374
- SO, I JUST TALKED
TO FRANKLIN,

11:34.480 --> 11:35.856
AND HE'S GONNA DO IT.

11:35.970 --> 11:37.688
HE SAID HE'D COME UP
FROM L.A. ANY TIME WE WANT TO,

11:37.800 --> 11:40.030
AND HE'LL BE OUR WITNESS
AT CITY HALL.

11:40.140 --> 11:44.179
- OH, OH.

11:44.280 --> 11:45.554
GOD, THAT'S SO NICE.
I'M SO GLAD.

11:45.670 --> 11:47.695
- BUT?

11:47.810 --> 11:49.289
- MY MOM.

11:49.390 --> 11:51.187
AFTER TALKING TO MY MOM,
I JUST FEEL LIKE SHE'S GOING

11:51.290 --> 11:52.461
TO WANT TO BE A PART
OF IT NOW.

11:52.570 --> 11:54.458
IT WAS A REALLY GOOD
CONVERSATION, AND I FEEL LIKE--

11:54.570 --> 11:56.629
- OH, THAT'S GREAT, I'M GLAD
THAT YOUR MOM'S ON BOARD.

11:56.750 --> 11:57.842
THAT'S REALLY IMPORTANT.

11:57.950 --> 11:59.463
- BUT--BUT SO,

11:59.580 --> 12:03.289
I WAS THINKING MAYBE
WE COULD HAVE A REAL CEREMONY

12:03.410 --> 12:05.549
NOW THAT THINGS ARE,
LIKE, ON BOARD, YOU KNOW?

12:05.650 --> 12:06.992
- YEAH.

12:07.100 --> 12:08.442
- IS THAT OKAY?
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW.

