WHEN I'M NOT ANGRY,

14:11.570 --> 14:13.458
WHICH IS REALLY WEIRD.
- THAT'S NOT A WEIRD NICKNAME.

14:13.570 --> 14:14.707
THAT'S A COOL NICKNAME.
- THAT'S A GREAT NICKNAME, MAX.

14:14.810 --> 14:16.698
- WELL, SPEAKING OF BAGGAGE,

14:16.820 --> 14:18.299
I HAVE A LITTLE ANNOUNCEMENT
TO MAKE.

14:18.400 --> 14:20.709
- OH?
- YES.

14:20.820 --> 14:23.095
MY ART CLASS IS
TAKING A TRIP.

14:23.200 --> 14:25.612
- OH, COOL.
- WE'RE GOING TO ITALY.

14:25.720 --> 14:27.688
- WHAT?
- THAT'S GREAT.

14:27.790 --> 14:29.303
- WOW.
- THAT'S GREAT, CAMILLE.

14:29.420 --> 14:31.411
- WELL, IT'S LIKE A RETREAT.
A WORKSHOP.

14:31.520 --> 14:33.750
- HOW LONG?
- A MONTH.

14:33.870 --> 14:35.417
- DAD, THIS IS LIKE
YOUR DREAM VACATION.

14:35.520 --> 14:37.283
IN YOUR SPEEDO,
ON THE MEDITERRANEAN,

14:37.390 --> 14:40.143
EATING PASTA
WHILE MOM WORKS ALL DAY,

14:40.250 --> 14:41.239
SPILL SOME ON YOUR CHEST--

14:41.360 --> 14:43.328
- ACTUALLY, DAD'S NOT GOING.
- WHAT?

14:43.430 --> 14:46.661
- DAD'S NOT GOING.

14:46.780 --> 14:47.769
- YOU'RE NOT GOING?

14:47.880 --> 14:51.634
- DAD, WHAT'S THE DEAL?

14:51.750 --> 14:53.741
- IT'S JUST YOU?

14:53.850 --> 14:54.748
- JUST ME.

14:54.850 --> 14:59.810
- WHY AREN'T YOU GOING, POP?

14:59.930 --> 15:03.855
- WOULD YOU PASS
THE MASHED POTATOES, PLEASE?

15:03.970 --> 15:06.689
- YEP.

15:06.800 --> 15:10.008
- THANK YOU.

15:10.110 --> 15:10.622
- THIS BROCCOLI DISH
IS REALLY GOOD.

15:10.730 --> 15:11.651
- YES.

15:22.680 --> 15:23.874
- HI.

15:23.990 --> 15:27.118
- UH-OH.
WHAT'S THIS ONE GONNA COST ME?

15:27.230 --> 15:28.083
- WHAT?
- WHAT DO YOU NEED NOW?

15:28.200 --> 15:29.918
- I'M NOT HERE
TO BORROW ANYTHING.

15:30.030 --> 15:32.851
- I SHOULD START CHARGING YOU
FOR THIS.

15:32.960 --> 15:35.576
- NO, I JUST CAME TO VISIT.

15:35.690 --> 15:36.896
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

15:37.000 --> 15:39.924
- ALL RIGHT,
WELL, HOW ARE YOU?

15:40.040 --> 15:41.689
- I'M GOOD.

15:41.800 --> 15:42.937
HOW ARE YOU?

15:43.040 --> 15:44.894
- [laughs]

15:45.010 --> 15:45.965
AS USUAL, YOU KNOW.

15:46.080 --> 15:46.694
- YEAH.

15:46.800 --> 15:48.859
UM.

15:48.980 --> 15:52.700
LISTEN, I--

15:52.810 --> 15:56.018
1--

15:56.120 --> 15:57.872
WHAT AM I TRYING TO SAY?

15:57.990 --> 16:01.812
ITS SAD SOMETIMES
THAT IT'S OVER BETWEEN US.

16:01.920 --> 16:04.024
- YEAH.

16:04.130 --> 16:07.850
- BUT IT'S OVER.

16:07.960 --> 16:08.858
- I KNOW THAT.

16:08.960 --> 16:11.611
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

16:11.720 --> 16:13.233
- WE DISCUSSED THAT.
- RIGHT.

16:13.350 --> 16:14.612
- WE DISCUSSED THAT A WHILE AGO.

16:14.730 --> 16:16.869
- IT'S JUST THAT, YOU KNOW,

16:16.970 --> 16:19.416
MAX BEING HERE HAS BEEN
SO GREAT FOR HIM,

16:19.530 --> 16:23.762
AND HE FEELS
LIKE YOU'RE HIS BEST FRIEND.

16:23.870 --> 16:26.907
BUT THEN HE SAID A BUNCH
OF STUFF

16:27.020 --> 16:29.705
AT THE DINNER TABLE ABOUT US

16:29.810 --> 16:32.631
THAT WAS SO SURPRISINGLY
INTIMATE,

16:32.750 --> 16:35.014
FOR YOU TO HAVE TALKED TO HIM,

16:35.130 --> 16:40.614
AND SO I JUST WANTED TO MAKE
SURE THAT YOU,

16:40.720 --> 16:43.029
YOU KNOW, THAT YOU CAN'T BE
TALKING TO HIM ABOUT ME.

16:43.140 --> 16:44.949
- FIRST OF ALL,
HE WAS TALKING TO ME, OKAY?

16:45.070 --> 16:48.346
I'M SORRY THAT YOU CAME UP.

16:48.450 --> 16:49.064
- IT WASN'T THAT I CAME UP.

16:49.180 --> 16:52.035
IT WAS THE CONTENT OF--

16:52.140 --> 16:53.550
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT ME TO SAY.

16:53.660 --> 16:55.070
IT'S LIKE 20 QUESTIONS
WITH THIS KID, THAT'S ALL.

16:55.180 --> 16:56.283
- BUT, YOU'RE THE ADULT.

16:56.390 --> 16:56.936
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO GIVE HIM 20 ANSWERS.

16:57.050 --> 16:59.211
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

16:59.320 --> 17:01.117
- IT'S NOT LIKE I'M SITTING
WRITING YOU LOVE SONGS,

17:01.220 --> 17:02.289
AND SINGING IT TO HIM, OKAY?

17:02.400 --> 17:04.288
- I KNOW.

17:04.400 --> 17:06.982
I'M NOT SAYING THAT YOU ARE
DOING ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

17:07.090 --> 17:08.466
- YOU KNOW, HE CAME TO ME, MAX,

17:08.570 --> 17:10.151
AND I THOUGHT I WAS DOING
SOMETHING GOOD FOR THIS KID...

17:10.270 --> 17:13.956
- YOU ARE DOING SOMETHING GOOD.

17:14.060 --> 17:15.300
- I DON'T LIKE THIS, YOU KNOW.

17:15.410 --> 17:18.299
THIS IS--HE--LOOK--HE--
I GOT A BUSINESS TO RUN,

17:18.410 --> 17:20.139
AND MAYBE HE JUST
SHOULDN'T BE HERE,

17:20.240 --> 17:21.889
BECAUSE HE IS A LITTLE GRATING.

17:22.000 --> 17:22.853
- NO, DON'T, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I'M SAYING.

17:22.970 --> 17:25.063
I'M NOT SAYING
HE SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

17:25.180 --> 17:26.442
- WELL, I AM.
I AM SAYING THAT, OKAY?

17:26.560 --> 17:27.788
I GOT TO DO THINGS
AROUND HERE,

17:27.900 --> 17:28.867
AND I SHOULDN'T HAVE A KID
WALKING AROUND HERE, OKAY?

17:28.970 --> 17:30.972
THIS IS A BUSINESS.
IT'S A BUSINESS.

17:31.080 --> 17:33.241
- DON'T DO THIS.
- I GOT A JOB TO DO RIGHT NOW.

17:33.360 --> 17:36.909
I GOTTA DO A SHOOT RIGHT NOW.

17:37.020 --> 17:38.157
- OKAY.

17:49.480 --> 17:50.879
- [sighs]

17:51.000 --> 17:52.194
- ONE OF THOSE NIGHTS WHEN
YOU WOULD DANCE IN THE LIGHTS

17:52.310 --> 17:56.269
WHAT ABOUT THIS
ON THE WAY BACK DOWN

17:56.380 --> 17:59.269
- I MEAN, IT JUST--
IT SOUNDS--

17:59.380 --> 18:03.032
- THAT SOUNDS LIKE OLIVER ROME
IS BORING OLIVER ROME.

18:03.150 --> 18:05.527
- YEAH, WHICH I DID
NOT THINK WAS POSSIBLE.

18:05.630 --> 18:07.939
THIS IS EXACTLY WHY LABELS
GAVE ARTISTS DRUGS IN THE '705.

18:08.050 --> 18:10.905
- I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT TO DO FOR HIM.

18:11.020 --> 18:12.772
- HAVE YOU GUYS
EVER SEEN THEM LIVE?

18:12.880 --> 18:14.256
- UH, NO.
- MM-MM.

18:14.360 --> 18:17.500
- OKAY, I SAW THEM A COUPLE
OF TIMES AT THE RED DEVIL,

18:17.610 --> 18:18.429
AND IT WAS
ACTUALLY VERY GOOD.

18:18.540 --> 18:20.462
OLIVER HAD, LIKE,
A LOT OF ENERGY,

18:20.580 --> 18:22.127
AND HE WAS REALLY CHARISMATIC
AND STUFF.

18:22.230 --> 18:23.640
- REALLY?

18:23.750 --> 18:25.399
- WELL, APPARENTLY
HE DOESN'T FIND THE LUNCHEONETTE

18:25.510 --> 18:26.477
AS CONDUCIVE TO CREATIVITY
AS THE RED DEVIL.

18:26.580 --> 18:29.026
- NO.
- I DON'T KNOW HOW TO FIX THAT.

18:29.140 --> 18:31.586
- WELL I WAS
THINKING, ACTUALLY,

18:31.690 --> 18:32.486
I MEAN, YOU KNOW
HOW HE NEEDS, LIKE,

18:32.590 --> 18:34.626
HIS EGO STROKED
ALL THE TIME.

18:34.730 --> 18:35.515
- STROKED, YEAH.

18:35.630 --> 18:36.449
HE NEEDS,
LIKE A FOUR HAND MASSAGE

18:36.560 --> 18:37.868
WITH EXOTIC OILS
AND ENYA PLAYING.

18:37.970 --> 18:41.485
- RIGHT, SO WHY DON'T WE JUST
GIVE HIM THAT, AND YOU KNOW,

18:41.600 --> 18:44.046
GIVE HIM LIKE AN AUDIENCE
TO PERFORM TO HERE.

18:44.150 --> 18:44.878
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
RIGHT HERE IN THE STUDIO?

18:44.980 --> 18:46.117
- YEAH, PRETTY MUCH.

18:46.220 --> 18:48.324
- WELL, HOW MANY PEOPLE
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT?

18:48.430 --> 18:49.601
- I DON'T KNOW, AS MANY
AS WE COULD SQUEEZE IN.

18:49.710 --> 18:51.462
WE'LL MAKE THEM YOUNG AND HOT,
AND YOUNG AND HOT...

18:51.570 --> 18:52.150
- WELL, HOT'S NEVER A BAD THING.

18:52.260 --> 18:54.148
- I DON'T KNOW, AMBER.

18:54.270 --> 18:55.919
IT'S TOUGH ENOUGH
TO GET THESE FIVE GUYS TO FOCUS

18:56.030 --> 18:57.224
WHEN IT'S JUST THEM.

18:57.340 --> 18:58.546
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT
THROWING THEM A PARTY.

18:58.650 --> 18:59.878
- NO, NO, NOT A PARTY,
BUT, LIKE, AN ACTUAL CONCERT.

19:00.000 --> 19:01.786
SERIOUSLY, LIKE, HAVE IT JUST
BE A SPECIFIC EVENT

19:01.890 --> 19:04.654
TO RECORD THE SONG,
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

19:04.760 --> 19:05.658
- IT COULD WORK.

19:05.760 --> 19:07.341
I MEAN THAT'S WHAT
THE BLACK CROWES DID

19:07.450 --> 19:08.417
ON BEFORE THE FROST,
AND THAT'S A DAMN GOOD ALBUM.

19:08.520 --> 19:10.067
- IT'S A GREAT ALBUM.
- AND I DON'T KNOW,

19:10.180 --> 19:11.454
I'LL ORGANIZE IT AND STUFF.

19:11.560 --> 19:14.449
I MEAN, I HAVE THEIR WEBSITE
FINISHED AND EVERYTHING.

19:14.560 --> 19:15.356
- YOU FINISHED THE WEBSITE?

19:15.460 --> 19:16.973
- HERE. YEAH.
- YOU MADE THIS?

19:17.080 --> 19:18.661
- YEAH, I MEAN ZACK HELPED,

19:18.770 --> 19:19.907
BUT, I MEAN, THIS IS WHAT
THEY WANTED.

19:20.020 --> 19:21.328
- THAT LOOKS GREAT.

19:21.430 --> 19:22.738
- I MEAN, I'LL ORGANIZE
THE WHOLE THING, YOU KNOW.

19:22.850 --> 19:24.568
I'LL DO SOCIAL MEDIA STUFF,
AND GET THE WORD OUT THERE,

19:24.680 --> 19:26.363
AND FIND PEOPLE,
AND I'LL GET DRINKS AND STUFF,

19:26.470 --> 19:28.051
I MEAN, IF YOU LIKE THE IDEA.

19:28.160 --> 19:30.845
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

19:30.960 --> 19:32.507
- WHY NOT?
I'M UP FOR IT.

19:32.610 --> 19:33.781
- ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO FOR IT.

19:33.890 --> 19:34.788
- YEAH?
- LET'S DO IT.

19:34.890 --> 19:36.164
- YEAH?
- YEAH.

19:36.270 --> 19:37.783
- GREAT.

19:37.900 --> 19:39.060
- MAYBE WE COULD BRING MOM
AND DAD HERE AND SORT THIS OUT.

19:39.170 --> 19:41.377
- I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I DON'T UNDERSTAND

19:41.490 --> 19:42.309
WHY THEY'RE TAKING
SEPARATE VACATIONS AT ALL.

19:42.420 --> 19:43.239
- HAVE THEY EVER DONE
THAT BEFORE?

19:43.350 --> 19:45.625
- NO, SOMETHING MUST
HAVE HAPPENED.

19:45.730 --> 19:47.379
- THEY'RE CLEARLY IN A FIGHT.
- YOU THINK THEY'RE IN A FIGHT?

19:47.490 --> 19:48.627
- YOU THINK THEY'RE HAVING
A FIGHT?

19:48.730 --> 19:49.480
- IT'S PROBABLY JUST
BECAUSE IT WASN'T DAD'S IDEA

19:49.600 --> 19:50.077
TO GO TO ITALY.
- "I'M MAD AT YOU.

19:50.180 --> 19:52.216
I'M GOING TO ITALY"?

19:52.320 --> 19:53.491
- ITALY'S OUTSIDE
OF DAD'S COMFORT ZONE.

19:53.600 --> 19:54.828
- LISTEN, HERE'S EXACTLY
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

19:54.950 --> 19:57.180
HE'S POUTING RIGHT NOW
BECAUSE HE PROBABLY SUGGESTED,

19:57.290 --> 19:59.497
LIKE, GOING ON
SOME BALLPARK TOUR OF AMERICA,

19:59.610 --> 20:01.089
AND SHE SAID "NO,"
AND NOW HE'S POUTING.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.326
- YEAH, WELL,
HE CAN BE PRETTY STUBBORN.

20:02.440 --> 20:03.771
- YEAH, BUT WHO POUTS
ABOUT ITALY?

20:03.890 --> 20:04.879
JUST GO.
- DAD.

20:04.990 --> 20:06.503
- I JUST THINK THE TIMING SUCKS
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,

20:06.610 --> 20:07.645
WHY IS SHE GOING NOW WHEN

20:07.750 --> 20:09.854
THERE'S A GRANDBABY
ON THE GROUND?

20:09.960 --> 20:11.166
SHE'S NOT EVEN GOING TO BE HERE?

20:11.270 --> 20:12.544
- THE GOOD NEWS IS DAD
CAN BABY-SIT.

20:12.650 --> 20:14.299
- OH, YEAH.
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

20:14.420 --> 20:15.682
- WITHOUT MOM?
- WHAT ABOUT SHOPPING?

20:15.800 --> 20:18.371
DAD DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
HOW THE GROCERY STORE WORKS.

20:18.490 --> 20:19.309
- YEAH, WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO SIT DOWN...

20:19.420 --> 20:21.797
- WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO MAKE A GRID.

20:21.910 --> 20:23.241
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR DAD'S SCHEDULE.

20:23.360 --> 20:24.691
- I DON'T WANT
TO GO CHECKING ON HIM.

20:24.800 --> 20:25.494
NO, HE'S A PAIN IN THE ASS.
- NO, I DON'T HAVE TIME.

20:25.600 --> 20:27.147
I'M A FREE-LANCE
PHOTOGRAPHER.

20:27.260 --> 20:28.079
YOU NEVER KNOW
WHEN THE DOGS ARE GOING TO CALL.

20:28.190 --> 20:29.976
- WHY IS THIS ALL ABOUT DAD?

20:30.090 --> 20:32.638
WHAT ABOUT MOM?

20:32.740 --> 20:34.560
WHAT ABOUT MOM,
WHO'S TAKEN CARE

20:34.680 --> 20:38.537
OF EVERYONE ELSE HER WHOLE LIFE?

20:38.650 --> 20:40.197
AND, LET ME TELL YOU,
DAD DOESN'T LISTEN TO HER.

20:40.300 --> 20:41.858
WHEN SHE TELLS HIM
WHAT SHE NEEDS,

20:41.960 --> 20:42.813
HE DOESN'T LISTEN TO HER.

20:42.930 --> 20:44.545
AND SO SHE'S DOING
SOMETHING FOR HERSELF

20:44.650 --> 20:46.618
FOR THE FIRST TIME PROBABLY IN,
YOU KNOW,

20:46.720 --> 20:48.028
HOWEVER LONG
THEY'VE BEEN TOGETHER.

20:48.140 --> 20:49.368
SO SHE'S GOING TO ITALY.

20:49.480 --> 20:51.061
DAD CAN DAMN WELL DEAL WITH IT,
AND SO CAN YOU.

20:51.180 --> 20:53.648
I'M GETTING SUGAR.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.713
- OH.
- OH.

21:22.830 --> 21:23.615
- HEY, NATS.
- OH, HEY, WHAT'S UP?

21:23.730 --> 21:26.722
- NOTHING,
I WAS JUST WALKING,

21:26.830 --> 21:29.390
AND MY SISTER, ACTUALLY,
IS DOING THIS THING

21:29.490 --> 21:31.173
AT THE LUNCHEONETTE,
THE RECORDING STUDIO...

21:31.290 --> 21:32.211
- YEAH, YEAH.

21:32.320 --> 21:33.480
- WELL, THEY'RE DOING THIS THING

21:33.600 --> 21:34.828
WHERE THEY'RE RECORDING
A BAND,

21:34.940 --> 21:36.567
LIKE, A LIVE PERFORMANCE
IN FRONT OF PEOPLE.

21:36.670 --> 21:38.069
- THAT SOUNDS COOL.
WHAT BAND?

21:38.190 --> 21:40.181
- THEY'RE CALLED
ASHES OF ROME.

21:40.290 --> 21:42.292
- YEAH, I DON'T KNOW THEM.

21:42.400 --> 21:43.674
- YOU'D PROBABLY LIKE IT,
THOUGH.

21:43.780 --> 21:45.839
