32:58.420 --> 33:01.105
- HEY.

33:01.220 --> 33:02.596
HEARD IT'S A BIG DAY, HUH?

33:02.700 --> 33:03.837
THE ALTERNATOR'S GOING
IN TODAY, YOU KNOW.

33:03.940 --> 33:06.829
- YEP.
- YEP.

33:06.950 --> 33:11.159
UH-OH, YOU GOT THAT "ADAM
CONCERNED" LOOK ON YOUR FACE.

33:11.260 --> 33:13.364
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?

33:13.470 --> 33:14.869
- ITALY, DAD.

33:14.990 --> 33:15.979
- ITALY.

33:16.090 --> 33:17.296
OH, YOUR MOM'S
BIG TRIP, HUH?

33:17.400 --> 33:19.641
- YEAH, AND, UNDERSTANDABLY,
WE'RE ALL WONDERING

33:19.750 --> 33:20.603
WHY YOU'RE NOT GOING.

33:20.720 --> 33:22.574
- OH, YEAH.

33:22.690 --> 33:24.999
ALL OF YOU WONDERING.
YOU'RE THE DELEGATE, ARE YOU?

33:25.100 --> 33:27.307
- I AM, AND WE ALL KNOW THERE'S
GOT TO BE SOME BIGGER REASON

33:27.410 --> 33:28.729
WHY YOU DECIDED NOT TO GO.

33:28.830 --> 33:33.073
- I'M NOT GOING
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT TO GO.

33:33.180 --> 33:36.240
- ALL RIGHT, MAYBE IT'S NOT
ABOUT WHAT YOU WANT.

33:36.350 --> 33:37.590
MAYBE YOU NEED
TO THINK ABOUT

33:37.700 --> 33:38.667
WHAT MOM WANTS FOR A CHANGE.

33:38.770 --> 33:39.839
CAN YOU DO THAT FOR HER?

33:39.940 --> 33:40.975
- OH, MY GOD, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE SAYING THAT.

33:41.080 --> 33:42.809
- WHAT?
- HOLD IT, HOLD IT, HOLD IT.

33:42.910 --> 33:43.808
GIVE ME A HAND UP, WOULD YOU?

33:43.910 --> 33:46.185
PICK ME UP HERE.
- YEP.

33:46.300 --> 33:48.291
- OKAY, ADAM, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

33:48.400 --> 33:49.947
SHE WANTS TO SELL
THE HOUSE, YOU KNOW.

33:50.060 --> 33:51.948
YOUR MOTHER WANTS
TO SELL OUR HOUSE.

33:52.060 --> 33:52.958
- WHAT?
- YEAH.

33:53.060 --> 33:54.607
YEAH, YEAH.
OH YEAH.

33:54.720 --> 33:55.709
SHE TALKING LIKE, ALL OF A
SUDDEN WE'RE IN THE THIRD ACT

33:55.820 --> 33:58.687
OF OUR LIVES, AND, LIKE, WE'RE
DOING SOME KIND

33:58.790 --> 34:01.202
OF A PLAY OR SOMETHING, AND
SINCE WE'RE IN THE THIRD ACT

34:01.310 --> 34:03.961
OF OUR LIVES, WE SHOULD BE
MOVING INTO SOMETHING SMALLER,

34:04.070 --> 34:06.652
LIKE MAYBE A CONDO,
THAT'S SHAPED LIKE A BOX.

34:06.760 --> 34:08.102
- OKAY.

34:08.210 --> 34:10.622
- AND THEN WE CAN GO TO
ALL THESE CULTURAL AFFAIRS,

34:10.730 --> 34:12.903
AND WE CAN GO SEE MUSEUMS,
AND, BY THE WAY,

34:13.010 --> 34:14.454
WE CAN GET ON THE BART
TO GO DO THAT.

34:14.560 --> 34:15.595
- OKAY.

34:15.700 --> 34:16.940
- THAT'S WHAT SHE'S
TALKING ABOUT.

34:17.050 --> 34:18.358
WELL, THAT'S NOT MY LIFE.

34:18.470 --> 34:21.598
THIS HAPPENS TO BE MY LIFE,
AND THIS IS OUR HOME.

34:21.710 --> 34:25.294
- OKAY, I GET IT, OKAY?

34:25.400 --> 34:27.607
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH, I DON'T
WANT YOU TO SELL THE HOUSE.

34:27.720 --> 34:29.745
OKAY, BUT MAYBE WE CAN ALLOW MOM
A LITTLE SPACE TO JUST BE

34:29.860 --> 34:33.682
ABLE TO INTRODUCE THIS
FOR CONVERSATION, YOU KNOW?

34:33.790 --> 34:36.350
PLENTY OF COUPLES YOUR AGE
THINK ABOUT DOWNSIZING.

34:36.450 --> 34:37.894
- OH, NOW WAIT A MINUTE.
DID YOU SAY "OUR AGE"?

34:38.000 --> 34:39.968
- I DID.

34:40.070 --> 34:41.344
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN,
COUPLES "OUR AGE"?

34:41.450 --> 34:42.587
- YOU KNOW WHAT I'M
TALKING ABOUT, OKAY.

34:42.700 --> 34:43.621
SHE'S NOT COMING FROM
OUTER SPACE, HERE.

34:43.730 --> 34:45.413
IT'S, LIKE, PEOPLE
DO THAT, AND, LOOK,

34:45.530 --> 34:46.929
MAYBE YOU CAN JUST TABLE
THE HOUSE FOR RIGHT NOW,

34:47.050 --> 34:49.666
AND YOU CAN JUST
GO TO ITALY.

34:49.770 --> 34:51.704
HAVE THIS ADVENTURE
WITH YOUR WIFE, AND, YOU KNOW,

34:51.810 --> 34:53.425
THIS WILL BE HERE
FOR YOU WHEN YOU GET BACK,

34:53.530 --> 34:56.465
AND YOU CAN DEAL WITH IT,
BUT, DAD, YOU CAN GO AWAY.

34:56.570 --> 34:57.912
GET A LITTLE TIME,
A LITTLE PERSPECTIVE.

34:58.020 --> 34:59.942
- OH, COME ON, I'VE GOT
A LIFETIME OF PERSPECTIVE.

35:00.060 --> 35:01.504
I DON'T NEED PERSPECTIVE.
- GOD, DAD.

35:01.610 --> 35:02.360
I'M JUST ASKING YOU
TO SUCK IT UP AND BE A MAN,

35:02.470 --> 35:03.914
AND GO TO ITALY
WITH YOUR WIFE.

35:04.030 --> 35:06.260
- WHAT--YOU TELLING ME
TO SUCK IT UP?

35:06.380 --> 35:07.028
YOU'RE TALKING TO
YOUR FATHER LIKE THAT?

35:07.130 --> 35:09.132
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

35:09.240 --> 35:12.061
I WILL TELL YOU THE REAL REASON
I'M NOT GOING.

35:12.170 --> 35:13.205
- OKAY, TELL ME.
- OKAY, OKAY.

35:13.310 --> 35:14.516
I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

35:14.620 --> 35:17.828
I WAS NOT INVITED.

35:26.910 --> 35:28.184
- [sighs]

35:37.200 --> 35:38.167
- HMM.

35:49.630 --> 35:52.349
[phone rings]

35:52.460 --> 35:53.245
- HELLO.

35:53.350 --> 35:55.352
- HEY, IT'S JULIA.
- HEY.

35:55.460 --> 35:57.041
- I'M SORRY I DIDN'T
CALL YOU BACK UNTIL NOW.

35:57.150 --> 36:00.074
I ACTUALLY JUST FOUND
YOUR MESSAGES NOW.

36:00.190 --> 36:01.873
- THAT'S COOL.
HOW ARE YOU?

36:01.980 --> 36:04.039
- OH, FINE.

36:04.160 --> 36:05.809
JOB HUNTING,

36:05.920 --> 36:08.388
DOING A FEW THINGS AROUND THE
HOUSE BEFORE I PICK UP THE KIDS.

36:08.510 --> 36:09.738
- UH-HUH.

36:09.850 --> 36:10.839
HOW ARE YOU?

36:15.170 --> 36:18.515
- REALLY NOT GOOD.

36:18.620 --> 36:20.679
AND DON'T TELL ME THAT
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

36:20.790 --> 36:23.998
- I WOULD NEVER TELL YOU THAT,
"'CAUSE IT'S NOT," SAYS MY WIFE.

36:24.110 --> 36:25.725
SORRY.
THAT WAS LOW HANGING FRUIT.

36:25.830 --> 36:28.003
SHE'S ACTUALLY THE OPTIMIST
AROUND THIS HOUSE.

36:28.110 --> 36:30.351
SO WHAT'S GOING ON?
- I DON'T KNOW.

36:30.460 --> 36:31.427
I'M ALL OVER THE PLACE.

36:31.530 --> 36:34.977
I'M EITHER YELLING
AT MY KIDS,

36:35.080 --> 36:36.490
NOT COMMUNICATING
WITH MY HUSBAND

36:36.600 --> 36:38.773
IN THE TEN MINUTE WINDOWS
THAT WE HAVE,

36:38.880 --> 36:41.701
GENERALLY MAKING EVERYONE
MISERABLE INCLUDING MYSELF.

36:41.820 --> 36:43.128
THIS IS SOUNDING
WAY WORSE THAN I INTENDED,

36:43.230 --> 36:47.746
BUT IT'S BEEN A ROUGH WEEK.

36:47.860 --> 36:51.023
- YEAH, SAME HERE,
AND THEN MY PHONE RANG,

36:51.130 --> 36:53.644
AND IT SUDDENLY
GOT A LOT BETTER.

37:04.910 --> 37:06.002
- OH.
HELLO.

37:06.120 --> 37:07.382
- YEAH, I'M GONNA
MAKE THIS QUICK,

37:07.500 --> 37:08.455
AND I'M NOT GONNA COME IN.

37:08.570 --> 37:10.219
- I DIDN'T ASK YOU IN.

37:10.330 --> 37:12.560
- YEAH, UH, I WAS THINKING
ABOUT WHAT YOU SAID,

37:12.670 --> 37:15.980
ABOUT MAX, AND THE WHOLE
"BEST FRIEND" THING.

37:16.090 --> 37:19.298
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW--
FRIENDS, BEST FRIENDS, I DON'T--

37:19.400 --> 37:22.437
LABELS, THAT'S NOT ME.

37:22.550 --> 37:24.302
I LIKE HIM.
I LIKE MAX.

37:24.410 --> 37:26.617
SMART, TALENTED KID,
YOU KNOW,

37:26.720 --> 37:28.893
AND HE'S A CAMERA NERD,
LIKE I USED TO BE.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.752
- USED TO BE?

37:30.860 --> 37:31.201
- YOU STILL GOT IT.

37:31.310 --> 37:34.131
LOOK, HE'S EAGER.

37:34.250 --> 37:36.889
GOD, HE'S EAGER, THIS KID.

37:37.010 --> 37:39.217
I'M NOT SAYING
HE DOESN'T HAVE HIS MOMENTS,

37:39.320 --> 37:41.459
BUT I'M SHOWING HIM
THE ROPES,

37:41.560 --> 37:45.041
AND IT'S GOOD FOR HIM.

37:45.150 --> 37:47.289
AND IT'S GOOD FOR ME.

37:51.890 --> 37:54.199
SO THE KID STAYS.

37:54.300 --> 37:55.153
- THANK YOU.
- YEAH.

37:55.270 --> 37:59.809
- GOOD, THANK YOU.

37:59.930 --> 38:01.955
- AND BY THE WAY,
THERE WERE, LIKE, SEVEN OR EIGHT

38:02.070 --> 38:03.094
OTHER PICTURES OF YOU
I HAD SCATTERED AROUND.

38:03.210 --> 38:05.440
I GOT RID OF THEM
SO YOU WON'T COME UP

38:05.550 --> 38:07.302
IN CONVERSATION ANYMORE.

38:07.420 --> 38:09.627
- SHUT UP.

38:09.730 --> 38:11.209
- ALL RIGHT.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

38:11.320 --> 38:13.629
YOU DID YOUR HAIR DIFFERENT?

38:13.730 --> 38:14.970
IS YOUR HAI|\RIODIFFERENT?

38:15.080 --> 38:16.069
- OR YOUR TEETH--
DID YOU DO--

38:16.190 --> 38:18.215
- DID I DO MY TEETH DIFFERENT?

38:18.330 --> 38:19.945
NO, THEY'RE JUST MY TEETH.

38:20.050 --> 38:22.939
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
- I'M TRYING TO GET OUT.

38:23.050 --> 38:24.119
- OH, OKAY.

38:24.230 --> 38:26.084
- ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

38:26.200 --> 38:27.986
- YOU JUST SAY GOOD-BYE.

38:28.090 --> 38:29.466
- OKAY.
NO PEEKING, ALL RIGHT?

38:29.580 --> 38:31.719
- RYAN, WHAT IS THIS?

38:31.820 --> 38:32.570
I'M STRESSED OUT.
- DON'T LOOK!

38:32.680 --> 38:33.123
ARE YOU LOOKING?
- OKAY, I'M NOT.

38:33.240 --> 38:34.332
I DIDN'T.

38:40.930 --> 38:41.100
- OKAY,
OPEN THEM.

38:46.420 --> 38:48.172
_ THE FIRST TIME I ASKED YOU,
IT WAS IMPULSIVE,

38:48.290 --> 38:50.554
AND IT WAS SPUR
OF THE MOMENT,

38:50.670 --> 38:53.423
AND SINCE THEN I'VE HAD NOTHING
BUT TIME TO THINK ABOUT IT,

38:53.530 --> 38:56.351
AND I COULDN'T BE MORE SURE.

38:56.470 --> 38:59.109
MY LIFE CHANGED THE DAY
THAT I MET YOU,

38:59.230 --> 39:03.121
AND I DON'T WANT TO SPEND
ANOTHER DAY OF IT WITHOUT YOU.

39:03.230 --> 39:04.436
I LOVE YOU.

39:04.540 --> 39:05.950
I WANT YOU TO BE MY WIFE.

39:09.690 --> 39:10.645
- RYAN.

39:10.760 --> 39:13.649
- WHAT?
- THAT'S--WE CAN'T AFFORD THIS.

39:13.760 --> 39:16.445
- YES, OF COURSE WE COULD.
I SPENT MY COMBAT PAY ON IT.

39:16.560 --> 39:19.381
I WANTED TO SPEND IT ON
THE RIGHT THING, AND THIS IS IT.

39:19.490 --> 39:22.072
- THAT'S--THAT'S TOO MUCH.

39:22.180 --> 39:23.454
- NO, NO, NO.

39:23.560 --> 39:25.289
I GET EXTRA PAY
FOR ACTIVE DUTY,

39:25.390 --> 39:26.948
AND I WAS SAVING IT UP.

39:27.050 --> 39:27.971
I WANTED TO--

39:28.080 --> 39:29.638
- ARE YOU SURE?

39:29.740 --> 39:32.152
- I'VE NEVER BEEN SO SURE
OF ANYTHING, EVER.

39:32.260 --> 39:35.297
- HONEY, I--

39:35.400 --> 39:37.846
- IT'S OFFICIAL, ALL RIGHT?

39:44.690 --> 39:46.373
- HEY.

39:46.480 --> 39:49.278
- HEY, YOU.

39:49.380 --> 39:52.486
UM, YOU GONNA INVITE ME IN?

39:52.590 --> 39:54.626
OR SHOULD WE DO
ANOTHER ONE OF THESE?

39:54.730 --> 39:56.038
- OH, ALL RIGHT, YEAH.
- POUND THAT?

39:56.150 --> 40:00.041
- HA, HA, GREAT.

40:00.150 --> 40:01.424
I'M CONFUSED.

40:01.530 --> 40:03.589
HONESTLY, I MEAN...

40:03.710 --> 40:06.804
WE'RE FRIENDS, YOU KNOW.

40:06.920 --> 40:10.742
WE'RE ALSO MORE
THAN FRIENDS, YOU KNOW,

40:10.850 --> 40:12.260
AND YOU DON'T WANT
A BOYFRIEND,

40:12.370 --> 40:15.988
BUT THEN ALSO, YOU'RE HERE.

40:16.100 --> 40:18.239
- YES.

40:18.340 --> 40:20.968
- I GUESS I SHOULD
JUST STOP TALKING.

40:21.070 --> 40:21.991
- MM-HMM.

40:39.780 --> 40:41.259
- I DON'T KNOW WHY
YOU WON'T LET ME TAKE YOU.

40:41.360 --> 40:42.463
THERE'S STILL TIME, YOU KNOW.

40:42.570 --> 40:44.083
- BECAUSE THIS IS SO MUCH
EASIER,

40:44.200 --> 40:45.849
AND YOU GET TO GO BACK TO BED.

40:45.960 --> 40:48.474
- RIGHT.

40:48.580 --> 40:52.402
WELL, OKAY, WELL, I GUESS
IT'S ARRIVEDERCI

40:52.510 --> 40:53.329
OR CIAOOR WHATEVER.

40:53.450 --> 40:57.443
- JUST THESE TWO?
- YES, THAT'S IT.

40:57.550 --> 41:01.316
TRAVELING LIGHT.

41:01.420 --> 41:02.694
OKAY.

41:02.800 --> 41:04.654
LET ME JUST CHECK
I'VE GOT EVERYTHING.

41:04.770 --> 41:05.282
TICKETS, MY GLASSES.

41:05.390 --> 41:06.311
I'M GOOD.

41:06.420 --> 41:11.289
- YEAH.

41:11.390 --> 41:12.493
- OKAY.

41:29.310 --> 41:31.585
- OKAY.

41:31.690 --> 41:33.169
YOU BE CAREFUL, NELLIE.

41:58.550 --> 42:01.610
[security alarm wails]

42:04.520 --> 42:06.306
OH, COME ON.

42:06.420 --> 42:08.308
OH, MY GOD.

42:14.350 --> 42:16.045
[sighs]
